name: The Case of the Madman's Mask
The case of the Tree House Trap
Case of the Deadly Treasure Hunt
Case of the Widow's Desparate Gamble
The Case of the Juvenile Delinquent!

description: PART 1 of a new 3-part story arc that takes Elektra around the globe in the hunt for an elusive African she-dictator.
name: Power Play, Part 1

description: It's "How To" Month as we take a look behind the curtain and witness how Elektra tries to assassinate a ruthless African dictator in part 2 of this 3-issue story arc!
name: Power Play, Part 2

description: Elektra is on the run after failing to assassinate a ruthless African Dictator in this conclusion of a 3-part story arc.
name: Power Play, Part 3

description: In a high-rise over the city, three corporate bosses meet for drinks and dinner to talk golf, fine cigars, finer women, and the unsavory business of controlling the world, never expecting the tables are about to be turned...
name: Dead to Rights

description:
PROPHET & LOSS PART 1

Elektra is hired to assassinate the leader of a violent guerilla movement in a small indipendent island nation in Southeast Asia, close Taiwan.

But will Elektra be able to fulfill her contract when she realizes that the insane leader is just an 8-year old boy?
name: Prophet & Loss, Part 1

description:
PROPHET & LOSS PART 2

Deep in the jungle of island-nation Naou, Elektra must infiltrate the camp of a violent guerilla movement in order to fulfill her contract.
name: Prophet & Loss, Part 2

description: Elektra's plan to get rid of the eight-year-old boy who's believed to be a demon's reincarnation is taking form, while an army of farmers and revolutionary fighters descend from their cove to the capital of the island-nation Naou, to kill and destroy, and free their lands from the grasp of foreigner countries.
name: Prophet & Loss, Part 3

description:
FEVER PART 1

Elektra must take out a petty Russian mobster on Brighton Beach while fighting the mother of all Asian flu viruses.
name: Fever, Part 1

description: Elektra's next assignment was supposed to be a walk on the beach, literally ... taking out a Russian mobster in Brighton Beach. But something has shaken Elektra up, turning this easy hit into a life and death struggle.
name: Fever, Part 2

description: Overview Elektra must slice and dice her way through a slew of Russian mobsters while fighting off the mother of all Asian flu viruses.
name: Fever, Part 3

description: Elektra was being haunted by her past; her death, trip to hell and her love with Daredevil.
name: Dead Reckoning

description:
The second part of the Brotherhood kicks off where the first part ended. Mike is apologizing to his wife Becky for what happened at the end of the last issue. Becky is angry and a little frightened when talking to her husband. Telling Mike that what happened should’ve never happened at all let alone be the last time. Mike tells her he’s sorry again and that they’ll talk about it later as he leaves going to work you see his face turn angry.

We see Frank doing what he does best. The Punisher is mowing down criminal scum left and right taking no prisoners. The whole time Frank is doing this we get to see his thoughts and insight of why he fights his never ending war on crime. Frank hit a major stock pile of cocaine and proceeds to torch it knowing the police will be there any minute.

Andy is screaming about the coke being burned up. Mike drags him away and when he does so Andy tells him everything. The Punisher listening nearby hears every bit of the conversation. Andy and Mike continue talking and Mike finally knows that Andy is indebted to the mob and Mike tries to come up with a plan to save his partners’ life.

Mike ends up talking to a priest trying to clear his head. The Priest doesn’t give Mike the answers he is looking for. Mike returns home and sits in the dark with a bottle of liquor he just drank when he hears his wife opening the door calling his name. What happens next leaves Becky crawling out of the house and Mike with a gun contemplating suicide.
name: Brotherhood, Part Two

description: Detective Pearse wife has walked out on him after taking too much abuse. Mike tries to get her to come back by force until the Punisher stops him. Andy is still in trouble with the mob and Mike decides to use his own life's savings to try and save Andy's life. The mob is not happy about this since it’s not near enough money to pay off Andy's debt and the Punisher is watching the whole event play out with mixed emotions of whether or not he should just kill Pearse for beating his wife and Andy for being a crooked cop.
name: Brotherhood, Conclusion

description: The Punisher guns down a bunch of mafia scumbags at a card game with only one escaping, unfortunately for him the ghosts of his friends who were killed by the Punisher hound him for running away and not trying to help them. The Ghosts demand the Punisher be killed so they move on and rest in peace while the surviving mobster only wants to be left alone in his quest to find a giant squid. Finally the mobster gives in to the demands of the ghosts and goes after the Punisher setting up a trap. The trap worked. Unfortunately for the gangster he found his giant squid which killed him before he could kill Frank Castle.
name: Squid

description: Castle faces an underground gang of cultist cannibals.
name: Hidden, Part One

description: Elektra kills the punisher's potential victims before he can get to them. He later finds out that she is doing it because she is bored and has nothing better to do.
name: Elektra

description: Small town Sheriff, Steve Southall, petitions the Punisher for assistance in protecting the town from the gang of gun-runners headed their way. The Punisher knocks him back, knowing that with what he's got planned, the lawman can't be a part of. As the Punisher puts his plan into action, the Sheriff heads out to intercept the gang before they reach the town.
name: Streets Of Laredo Part 3

description:
The Punisher returns to Branding and discovers a badly beaten Sgt. Southall. Punisher cuts the Police Officer down from where he's been strung up by the gun runners that brought the Punisher to town. It's clear that Southall won't survive and there's still the matter of the gang's imminent return.

The Punisher sends a message, calling the gang out for a High Noon showdown. He aims to stop the gang's rampage and uncover the identity of the murderer whose actions engineered this bloody finale.
name: Streets Of Laredo Part 4

description: Detective Soap relates his life story to a new friend in his favourite bar, including details from his youth in orphanage, why he became a cop and how he became entangled with the Punisher.
name: Soap

description: Frank picks up a tip while taking out a group of Irish mobsters, there's a big auction taking place and whoever get what's on sale is going to rule the city. When his source runs dry, Franks hits the local crims and stoolies to look for more information about the auction. On his tail are Daredevil, Spider-man and Wolverine - all of whom have run afoul of the Punisher's war on crime on separate occasions and all keen to see him taken off the streets.
name: Confederacy Of Dunces, Part 1

description:
Overwhelmed by the possibility of facing Spider-Man, Wolverine and Daredevil in combat, The Punisher surprises them by opting to have a cheeseburger instead and biding his time to wait for an opportunity to give them the slip. It's a situation that he's able to expedite with a well placed elbow.

Free from his super-powered entanglement, Frank's attention is directed back to the underworld auction he'd been investigating. But what is it that they're selling?
name: Confederacy Of Dunces Part 2

description: The Punisher has the amnesiac man, who had been the subject of the underworld auction that the Punisher put a stop to, under lock and key. Daredevil, Wolverine and Spider-Man are still on the Punisher's case but he's not going to let that keep him out of Hell's Kitchen. In fact, that's where he's going to set his next trap for the three of them.
name: Confederacy Of Dunces Part 3

description: With his plan to incapacitate Daredevil undone, the Punisher has to improvise in order to retain the upper hand. He gives Daredevil a final warning - stop coming after him because he won't go easy on you next time. The Punisher knows that it's not going to stop them but he's got another plan for them the next time he sees them. It involves the amnesiac man he's been holding captive. He's someone they'll find familiar but they won't like him if he's angry.
name: Confederacy Of Dunces Part 4

description: The conclusion to the storyline "Confederacy of Dunces" and the last issue of the series. The Hulk is on the loose. Set upon Daredevil, Wolverine and Spider-Man by the Punisher. He's way beyond their power level and they're quickly outmatched. Good thing that all of that stew the Punisher had been feeding Banner contained a special ingredient or two. All part of the Punisher's plan to show the heroes the lengths he'll go to to keep them off his back. Meanwhile, Detective Soap is finally fed up enough to try and bring the Punisher in by himself.
name: Confederacy Of Dunces Part 5

description: Racist militia groups await the SOLDIER as he completes his long journey home. America's never looked so good, or so troubled.
name: Rebels, Freaks & Prophets - 1

description: Soldier X brings the battle to United States soil, fighting the very idea of a racist militia by any means necessary! The more important question: for a proselytizing Nathan, will he destroy the racists, or turn them to his will?
name: Rebels, Freaks & Prophets - 2

description: The final story of Soldier X begins when a young mutant is put on death row for killing her parents. What Nathan Summers discovers about the murder and the young mutant's fate will lead him to unravel a mystery involving the Weapon X Program and the strange disappearances of mutants all over the country.
name: Dead Ends - 1

description: SOLDIER X ends with Nathan Summers solving a mystery involving the Weapon X Program and the strange disappearances of mutants all over the country. Series Finale!
name: Dead Ends  - 2

description:
Fight-Bolts!!

It's "Fight Club" meets Marvel as writer John Arcudi (JLA) and penciler Francisco Ruiz Velasco (Lone Wolf 2100) kick off a new direction for THUNDERBOLTS! No jail breaks; no stolen moneybags with dollar signs on them; no running away to strike another day. This is what happens to super-villains without hope. They take a voyeuristic look at a world of bloody fights in abandoned warehouses, the lure of easy money, and the desperate smell of sweaty losers. If you're trying to do the right thing, do you stay bitter in your lousy day job... or make one last grab for fame -- by busting heads?
name: Bare Knuckle

description: Issue Two of the T-Bolts' radical new direction! Watch the slow disintegration of a man on the edge! Rather then falling back into a life of crime or sticking with your crappy day job, maybe the worst day will instead provide a last change for Ö something else? More drinking, swearing and fighting in the Mighty Marvel Manner! And check out that cover!
name: How to lose

description: The controversial revamp of the Thunderbolts continues! Axum is forced to make a hard choice, does he walk the straight & narrow line, or does he cross it and never look back?
name: How does it feel?

description: The controversy continues as the new T-Bolts first story arc concludes! Meet the champ of the underground fighting league, and then see if he makes it out of this issue alive!
name: Play the Odds

description: Man-Killer joins Axum's fighting club, and invites Axum to join in a reformation of the Masters of Evil.
name: Getting Even

description: FINAL ISSUE! In Part 2 of the story starring Spider-Man, the choices Axum must make coincide with the presence of a figure familiar to the classic T-Bolts: Man-Killer, as well as the Scorpion.
name: Getting even more!

description: X-Men Unlimited goes bi-weekly with a new LOWER-PRICED format! Because YOU demanded it. Chris Claremont and Bill Sienkiewicz reteam for an All-New NEW Mutants story! Plus, Steven Grant and Paul Smith explain where every X-fan's favorite dragon LOCKHEED has been.
name: Keepsake / Lockheed the Dragon

description: The bi-weekly action continues! Not all of the battles the X-MEN fight have the fate of the world hanging in the balance - some are much more important. This issue, the X-MEN take a stand against animal cruelty.
name: Can They Suffer?

first_appearance_locations.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

location_credits.name: Jean Grey School for Higher Learning

description: A tie-in with this month's UNCANNY X-MEN. Alpha Flight's in full force, and expanding their roster! Witness the birth of Vindicator's and Guardian's baby!
name: Hero

description: Wolverine blowout issue! Marvel's bad boy is back in true lethal form in two hardcore stories!
name: Weapon of Choice / Upon Reflection

description: The Return of Psylocke! A blast from the past as the X-Men's sexy psychic ninja flies solo! Written by Adam Warren with art by Rick Mays! The second story feature an eye- popping Cyclops tale brought to you by John Layman and Dan Norton!
name: Bloody 'Ell / Strange Harvest

description: Mystique returns, but defying all expectations! Just what is the sultry shape-changer doing in the employ of Nick Fury and S.H.I.E.L.D.? Find out in this globetrotting adventure by Chuck Austen and Chris Cross! And in a fully painted story by Richard Isanove, Bruce Jones takes us back to the Savage Land where Wolverine and Shanna the She-Devil duke it out in a madcap misunderstanding.
name: Untitled / Control

description: FABLES writer Bill Willingham brings you a full-issue swashbuckling adventure featuring the irrepressible Nightcrawler!
name: Untitled

description: A Wolverine story from Kazuo Koike (Lone Wolf  and Cub) and Paul Smith (Uncanny X-men), and four manga-style X-men pin-ups.
name: The Swordsmith

description: Who's stronger? Well, friends, you're about to find out, as America’s favorite mutants go toe-to-toe with Earth’s Mightiest Heroes: the Avengers! In part three, Vivisector squares off against Hawkeye, while Venus puts the squeeze on Ant-Man!
name: The Good And The Famous, Part 3: Vivisector Vs. Hawkeye

description: Who's stronger? Well, friends, you're about to find out…as America’s favorite mutants go toe-to-toe with Earth’s Mightiest Heroes, the Avengers! In part four, Mister Sensitive squares off against Iron Man!
name: The Good And The Famous, Part 4

description: Who's stronger? Well, friends, you're about to find out…! America’s favorite mutants go toe-to-toe with Earth’s Mightiest Heroes -- the Avengers! In part three, Doop squares off against The Mighty Thor! Ouch!
name: The Good And The Famous, Part 5

description:
The team embarks on its most hazardous mission yet! No, we’re not exaggerating. We mean it. Break out the tissues, and zip up the bodybags in this extra-special, last issue of the title formerly known as X-FORCE.

In the final issue of Peter Milligan's X-Force / X-Statix opus, the cast is given what is, true to the cover's advertising, a 'downbeat yet strangely touching' send-off.

The Orphan, The Anarchist and Dead Girl would resurface a year later in the 5-issue 'X-Statix Presents: Dead Girl' limited series. Doop, in some form, would resurface briefly during Peter Milligan's run on X-Men.
name: Are You Ready?

description: Lucas joins a posse after the Cattleman's Association is robbed of $3,000. Meanwhile Mark goes fishing at a nearby creek. The posse finds the robbers and Lucas wings one of them and his horse bolts. Mark finds the horse and takes him home. When Lucas returns he finds the stolen money and takes it to the sheriff. After he leaves the robbers come by looking for a horse and Mark stalls them until Lucas returns.
name: The Rifleman
Jace Pearson's Tales of the Texas Rangers
